### 5. Ansible Configuration

#### Install Ansible
```bash
# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y

# Verify installation
ansible --version
```

#### Configure Dynamic Inventory
```bash
cd ansible/

# Install boto3 for AWS dynamic inventory
pip install boto3 botocore

# Test dynamic inventory
ansible-inventory -i inventory/aws_ec2.yaml --list
```

#### Run Ansible Playbook
```bash
# Test connectivity
ansible all -i inventory/aws_ec2.yaml -m ping

# Run playbook to configure Jenkins server
ansible-playbook -i inventory/aws_ec2.yaml playbook.yaml

# Verify Jenkins installation
# Access Jenkins at http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP:8080
```

#### Ansible Roles

**Common Role:**
- Updates system packages
- Installs Git, Docker, Java (OpenJDK 11)
- Configures system settings

**Jenkins Role:**
- Adds Jenkins repository
- Installs Jenkins
- Starts and enables Jenkins service
- Retrieves initial admin password

