### 7. ArgoCD Continuous Deployment

#### Install ArgoCD
```bash
# Create namespace
kubectl create namespace argocd

# Install ArgoCD
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

# Wait for pods to be ready
kubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=600s deployment --all -n argocd
```

#### Access ArgoCD UI
```bash
# Get initial admin password
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d

# Port forward to access UI
kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443

# Access UI at https://localhost:8080
# Username: admin
# Password: (from command above)
```

#### Deploy Application via ArgoCD
```bash
# Apply ArgoCD application manifest
kubectl apply -f argocd/application.yaml

# Check application status
kubectl get application -n argocd

# Sync application
kubectl patch application ivolve-app -n argocd --type merge -p '{"operation":{"initiatedBy":{"username":"admin"},"sync":{}}}'
```

#### ArgoCD Configuration

**Sync Policy:**
- **Automated**: Automatically syncs when Git repository changes
- **Prune**: Removes resources deleted from Git
- **Self-Heal**: Reverts manual changes to match Git state

**Source:**
- Repository: Your GitHub repository
- Path: `kubernetes/` directory
- Revision: `HEAD` (main branch)

**Destination:**
- Cluster: In-cluster (where ArgoCD is installed)
- Namespace: `ivolve`

