## Usage Guide

### Complete Workflow

#### 1. Developer Workflow
```bash
# Make changes to application code
vim app/app.py

# Commit and push
git add .
git commit -m "Updated application feature"
git push origin main
```

#### 2. Automated CI/CD Flow
1. **Jenkins Pipeline Triggers:**
   - Detects Git push via webhook/polling
   - Builds new Docker image
   - Tags with build number
   - Pushes to DockerHub
   - Updates Kubernetes manifests
   - Pushes manifest changes to Git

2. **ArgoCD Deployment:**
   - Detects manifest changes in Git
   - Syncs with Kubernetes cluster
   - Deploys new version with rolling update
   - Self-heals if manual changes occur

#### 3. Verify Deployment
```bash
# Check pods
kubectl get pods -n ivolve

# Check service
kubectl get svc -n ivolve

# View logs
kubectl logs -f deployment/ivolve-web -n ivolve

# Check ArgoCD sync status
kubectl get application ivolve-app -n argocd
```

### Accessing the Application

#### Local (Minikube)
```bash
minikube service ivolve-svc -n ivolve
```

#### AWS (EKS)
```bash
# Get LoadBalancer URL
kubectl get svc ivolve-svc -n ivolve -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].hostname}'
```

### Manual Deployment

#### Build and Deploy Manually
```bash
# Build image
docker build -t YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/ivolve:manual .

# Push image
docker push YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/ivolve:manual

# Update deployment
kubectl set image deployment/ivolve-web ivolve=YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/ivolve:manual -n ivolve

# Verify rollout
kubectl rollout status deployment/ivolve-web -n ivolve
```

